

Variables
==========

Local varibales 
Instance varibles 
static varibales 


local variables 
================

Declared inside methods, constructors, or blocks
Exist only during the execution of that block
Must be initialized before useâ€”no default values
Not accessible outside the method or block
Stored in stack memory

Instance variables
==================

- Declared inside a class but outside any method
- Belong to the object (instance) of the class
- Each object gets its own copy
- Can have default values (e.g., 0 for int, null for objects)
- Stored in heap memory

Static variables
================

Declared with the  keyword inside a class
Shared across all instances of the class
Belong to the class, not to any object
Useful for constants or shared counters
stored in method area 
